  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was just him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He never said anything about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] When I was a kid-- when I was a kid, about eight years old, he gave me a job plucking feathers off of chickens because, you know, in our community, everybody had fried chicken every Sunday.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So people bought a lot of chickens, and I took the feathers off the chicken and he showed me how to do it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he gave me a little job doing that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I got to know his-- his daughter and his son very well, because they were a little younger than me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the whole family was just very nice.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They went to the Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went to-- when I-- you mean at grade school?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were several people that I finally became friends with.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Fellow-- there was a fellow named Jack Gardner who-- who later-- later became the associate dean at the Medical school at Rutgers.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a fellow named Tom Waller who, we were inseparable for a while.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was-- he became a police officer in Chicago.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then, there were several-- several other people that I knew but those were the two fellows that I was closest-- that I was closest with.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh and another fellow.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a fellow, Maurice [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Neisler. ?] And [LAUGHS] my mother was never comfortable with that relationship, mainly because she saw Maurice as a person who would get me into trouble, not from a standpoint of the street kind of trouble, but because I was always trying to protect him from people assaulting him.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was one of those kids that everybody wanted to just chase for some reason, and I was always the guy there stopping them.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
